'''Mallamada Narendra Ponnamma''' (born 25 October 1992) is an Indian [[field hockey]] player, who plays as a [[Field hockey#Positions|halfback]] for the [[India women's national field hockey team|Indian national team]]. She was a part of the team that won bronze at the [[2013 Women's Hockey Junior World Cup|2013 Junior World Cup]], in [[Germany]].<ref name="tnie">{{cite news|last1=Sreekumar|first1=S. S.|title=Ponnamma: Creating history|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/bengaluru/Ponnamma-Creating-history/2013/08/22/article1745280.ece|accessdate=9 November 2015|work=The New Indian Express|date=22 August 2013}}</ref>

==Early life and career==
Ponnamma was born on 25 October 1992 in [[Kodagu district]], in the Indian State of [[Karnataka]], into Mallamada family of the [[Kodava people|Kodava]] community. Born to a family of hockey players, her father Narendra, played hockey during his time in the Indian armed forces; her mother, during her college days; and her older sister, who gave up the game after sustaining an injury.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chinnappa|first1=K. Jeevan|title=Ponnamma upholds Kodagu’s hockey tradition|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/ponnamma-upholds-kodagus-hockey-tradition/article5017759.ece|accessdate=9 November 2015|work=The Hindu|date=13 August 2013}}</ref> Influenced towards the game by her father, Ponnamma was selected by and began training with [[Madikeri]] branch of [[Sports Authority of India]], in 2005.<ref name="tnie"/> After having been noticed for her performances at tournaments at the district level, she was chosen to play for Karnataka in its senior team, at the national-level, and would go on to captain the team as well. She was eventually chosen to represent India in its junior and senior teams, in 2011.

